# This is a BLUEPRINT, not a live deployment. Its subproject env files
# (web/.web.env, api/.api.env) hold only port numbers — no secrets — and are
# deliberately committed so the example stays runnable out of the box and the
# smoke test (test/smoke-monorepo.sh) can copy + assert against them.
#
# The repo-root .gitignore ignores `.*.env`; re-include the blueprint's own
# demo env files here so they are tracked. A REAL project would NOT do this —
# real runtime env files (and any secrets) stay gitignored.
!web/.web.env
!web/.web.dev.env
!web/.web.prod.env
!api/.api.env
!services/reports/.reports.env

# A real .env / .secrets.env created by trying the example (cp example.env .env)
# must still stay ignored — re-assert that for this dir.
.env
.secrets.env
*.secrets.env
